## Where to place these in your repo

```
apps/mobile/assets/images/welcome/
  ├── welcome-family.jpg
  ├── welcome-family@2x.jpg
  ├── welcome-horizon.jpg
  └── welcome-horizon@2x.jpg
```

Source files (masters) should NOT be in the app bundle. Keep them archived elsewhere — outside the repo or in a `.gitignore`d folder. Only the four `welcome/*.jpg` files ship to users.

---

## Naming convention going forward

When you create new variations from these source files (blurred for empty states, cropped for marketing, etc.), follow this pattern:

```
welcome-{purpose}.jpg          ← 1x
welcome-{purpose}@2x.jpg       ← Retina

Examples:
welcome-family-blur.jpg        ← Heavily blurred for cards
welcome-horizon-tight.jpg      ← Cropped tight for empty states
welcome-family-dim.jpg         ← Pre-dimmed for final CTA
```

For non-welcome surfaces (settings, about, hub):

```
{screen}-{purpose}.jpg

Examples:
about-hero.jpg
hub-banner.jpg
empty-state.jpg
```

