## When porting to React Native

Reference these in code as:

```jsx
const FAMILY_PHOTO = require('../../assets/images/welcome/welcome-family.jpg');
const HORIZON_PHOTO = require('../../assets/images/welcome/welcome-horizon.jpg');

// Expo will auto-resolve @2x for retina devices
```

For backgrounds, use `expo-image` (faster + better caching than React Native's `Image`):

```jsx
import { Image } from 'expo-image';

<Image
  source={FAMILY_PHOTO}
  style={StyleSheet.absoluteFill}
  contentFit="cover"
  transition={1000}
/>
```

For glass cards, use `expo-blur`:

```jsx
import { BlurView } from 'expo-blur';

<BlurView intensity={50} tint="dark" style={cardStyle}>
  {/* card contents */}
</BlurView>
```

